Case set for sentencing hearing. Parties are prepared to proceed. PSI reviewed by the parties. Statements made as to sentencing. Additional statements made by Madeline R., Ivilsse Q.

As to COUNT 1-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 6 YEARS, concurrent with case 14CF3343, with credit for 49 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 4 YEARS.  

Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Earned Release Program. The defendant is not appropriate for the Substance Abuse Program.

Court costs, fees, surcharges and restitution be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
1) Register and comply with the sex offender registry;
2) Obtain/comply with sex offender treatment; 
3) No unsupervised contact with children under the age of 16 years, including family members;
4) No contact with the victim. Court will allow contact with the victims mother as long as she approves;
5) Pay restitution in the amount of $528.00 to Madeline R. Restitution to be paid first before costs;
6) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
7) Provide DNA sample (unless previously submitted) and pay surcharge;
8) No social media accounts. Defendant may maintain an email account;
9) Any electronic devices must be turned over to agent for inspection upon demand;
10) No employment where children under the age of 16 years are present;
11) Attend anger management classes;
12) Attend cognitive thinking class;
13) AODA assessment and comply with any recommended treatment;

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession; Voting and Child sex offender working with children.

